ABAKALIKI – Governor of Bauchi State, Bala Mohammed, has said the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) is set to take back power from the ruling All Progressives Congres (APC) come 2023. Mohammed, who stated this on Friday in Abakali­ki, Ebonyi State, when he visited to consult Ebonyi PDP delegates, said the PDP had several eminent­ly qualified presidential as­pirants, capable of taking Nigeria out of the wood if elected president in 2023. He described APC’s led Federal Government as an aberration and a huge ob­struction to the growth and development of Nigeria. -Advertisement- The presidential hope­ful said Nigerians only witnessed democracy during the regimes of for­mer President Olusegun Obasanjo and former Pres­ident Goodluck Jonathan. He said President Mu­hammadu Buhari’s regime was characterised with nepotism, discrimination, bad governance, and cor­ruption at its highest level. He said under him as FCT Minister, he solved the problem of the poor road network, and assured that if given the opportunity to preside over the affairs of Nigeria, he would turn things around positively. “We are coming back to take back power. We have so many candidates in the PDP and we are all emi­nently qualified to Nigeri­ans the kind of governance they want. “But, the take away that brought me to Ebonyi is for you to know me, the opportunity to know the country and for you to see me and hear me. In FCT, we reduced the trouble times by bringing good roads. POLL “The APC administra­tion is an aberration, is an obstruction to our growth and development. “Only the years Nigeri­ans knew that there was democracy was during Obasanjo and during Jon­athan. Yes, what happen in this regime is nepo­tism, corruption, discrim­ination, bad governance, corruption at its highest level,”he said.